# CHANGELOG.md Guide

Maintain the project's changelog to track all user-facing changes.

## Format

Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format:

```markdown
# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).

## [Unreleased]

### Added
- New features

### Changed
- Changes to existing functionality

### Fixed
- Bug fixes

### Deprecated
- Soon-to-be removed features

### Removed
- Removed features

### Security
- Security vulnerability fixes

## [1.0.0] - 2026-01-15

### Added
- Initial release
```

## When to Update

1. **During development** (before merging PR):
   - Add entry under `[Unreleased]` section
   - Use category: Added / Changed / Fixed / Deprecated / Removed / Security
   - One bullet point per user-facing change

2. **When releasing** (before creating release tag):
   - Replace `[Unreleased]` with `[VERSION] - YYYY-MM-DD`
   - Create new `[Unreleased]` section at top
   - Commit with message: `chore(changelog): release vX.Y.Z`

## Examples

### Adding a Feature

```markdown
## [Unreleased]

### Added
- New search filters on job board
- Support for resume upload (PDF/DOCX)
```

### Fixing a Bug

```markdown
## [Unreleased]

### Fixed
- Fixed crash when parsing malformed job listings
```

### Deprecating API

```markdown
## [Unreleased]

### Deprecated
- `/api/v1/search` endpoint (use `/api/v2/search` instead)
```

## Tips

- Be concise: 1–2 lines per entry
- Write for end users: "Added resume upload" not "Added file upload handler"
- Group related changes together
- Keep entries in reverse chronological order within each category
